# Copy to .env.local for local development. Never commit real values —
# see .gitignore.
#
# This app is a static SPA with no backend yet (see ARCHITECTURE.md's
# Commerce Engine section). A real PaymentProvider implementation will
# need a server-side home (a Vercel serverless function or a separate
# backend) for its SECRET key — a provider's secret key must never be a
# VITE_-prefixed variable, since Vite inlines every VITE_ variable into
# the public client bundle. No PaymentProvider is implemented yet; these
# are placeholders for the sprint that adds the first one.

# --- Client-safe (VITE_ prefixed — inlined into the public bundle) ---
# A provider's PUBLISHABLE key only (e.g. Stripe's pk_*) — safe to expose
# client-side.
# VITE_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# --- Server-only (never VITE_ prefixed — must live wherever the
# server-side PaymentProvider implementation eventually runs, never in
# this client bundle) ---
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=
